**a.)** Here, the question asks for the current value of the firm. Since it is stated in the problem that the firm does not have debt, then it means we are solving for the unlevered firm value. To do this, we will use this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Unlevered firm value}&=\dfrac{\text{Earnings before interest and tax}\times (1-\text{Tax rate})}{\text{Cost of equity}}
\end{aligned}$$

For the second scenario where the debt is equal to the whole levered firm value, we will get:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Levered firm value}&=\$221,236.26\\
&+0.22\times \text{Levered firm value}
\end{aligned}$$
